The article discusses the upcoming Fourth of July celebration in the United States. It mentions that Americans have always valued their freedom and have honored those who sacrificed their lives to defend it. The article highlights the historical significance of July 4, 1776, when the Declaration of Independence was adopted. It also mentions that President Thomas Jefferson held the first Fourth of July event at the White House in 1801, and this tradition has been continued by modern Presidents. The article states that this year, President Trump will deliver remarks from the South Lawn of the White House during the "Salute to America" event. The celebration will include the participation of members of the military, first responders, healthcare workers, and other heroes who fought against the Coronavirus pandemic. Festivities will include music, military demonstrations, flyovers, and a fireworks display.